{
  "text": "(1), MOPS (10), Phosphocreatine (10). The pH was adjusted to 7.0 using KOH. Potassium Proprionate (Kprop) was added to adjust the final ionic strength to 180 mM. Contaminant P i was reduced by adding the enzyme purine nucleoside phosphorylase with the substrate 7-methyl guanosine which acts as an P i scavenging system [CITATION_1] . A range of free [Ca [CITATION_2] , and the enzymes Pyruvate Kinase (4 mg/mL;500 U/mg) and Lactate Dehydrogenase (0.24 mg/mL;870 U/mg). Solutions were adjusted to pH 7.0 using KOH. Calcium free extra-cellular solution contained (in mmol/L): TRIS (50), NaCl (100), KCl (2), MgCl 2 (2), EGTA (1). The pH was adjusted to 7.0 using HCl. Rigor solution contained (in mmol/L): TRIS (50), KCl (100), MgCl 2 (2), EGTA (1); pH was adjusted to 7.0 using HCl.",
